{
  "stem": "3952.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we would-- my mother took the sugar and my father and they weighed it out in portions of kilos.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we-- and I went to all-- I and my little sister, we went to all the Jewish houses, and we sold to everybody a kilo or two of sugar, and we made money.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we bought everything that we needed for Pesach.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And whenever we meet our brothers and sisters, when we're together, we always remember the Pesach, the-- the happy Pesach that we had.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So if you want to call that a happy moment, yes, that Pesach was happy because the misery was so big.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just two days earlier, we didn't know how we will make the Pesach-- the Seder-- the Seder night.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And now suddenly we had the matzot and the potatoes and whatever we needed for Pesach.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a happy, happy moment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then after Pesach, I think this was the last Pesach, actually, that we were free people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Immediately, the-- the next Sunday after Pesach, it was the 9th of May, which I didn't remember, except that my-- now my sister sends me some pictures, and she writes on the 9th of May, we were deported.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1944.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So in the 9th of May, we were taken to-- to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were there for two weeks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were taken-- we-- we had to prepare-- they told us to prepare where to take the luggage, a cart.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, a cart with-- with oxen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all the neighbors, all the neighbors in that courtyard, we lived nine Jewish neighbors.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So all the neighbors used the same car, put it in on the-- put the valise, when there was no room, the rest we were carrying by hand.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
